						<summary>

						<p>On a slab set up in front of Maḷigēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Rāmachandra, 1291 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1213, Khara, Śrāvaṇa śu. 1, Sunday, corresponding to 1291 A.D., July 30. The weekday, however, was Friday.</p>						

						<p>It seems to register a gift to a deity by a chief. As the inscription is badly damaged and worn out, most of the details are lost.</p>						

						</summary>
